problems.statement:
Let $A = \{(x,y) \in \mathbf{R}^2 : x < 0, \text{ or } x \geq 0 \text{ and } y \neq 0\}$.
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(a)] If $f: A \to \mathbf{R}$ and $D_1 f = D_2 f = 0$, show that $f$ is constant. \textit{Hint:} Note that any two points in $A$ can be connected by a sequence of lines each parallel to one of the axes.
\item[(b)] Find a function $f: A \to \mathbf{R}$ such that $D_2 f = 0$ but $f$ is not independent of the second variable.
\end{enumerate}

Define $f: \mathbf{R}^2 \to \mathbf{R}$ by
$$f(x,y) = \begin{cases} xy\dfrac{x^2-y^2}{x^2+y^2} & (x,y) \neq 0, \\ 0 & (x,y) = 0. \end{cases}$$
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(a)] Show that $D_2 f(x,0) = x$ for all $x$ and $D_1 f(0,y) = -y$ for all $y$.
\item[(b)] Show that $D_{1,2} f(0,0) \neq D_{2,1} f(0,0)$.
\end{enumerate}
